Hannah Brierley thought her mother was playing a prank when she spotted the northern pine snake on a bath mat at her home in Rochdale . 
  Her mother Karen Marriott couldn't get hold of the RSPCA so called the police to help . 
  Det Con Craig Wallace overheard the call and used a pillowcase to capture the reptile . 
  He believes it may be a family pet that escaped or was set free . 
 